's a different artifact. This is indeed a form of test-code setup guidance. The final JSON includes that no special environment properties are needed for core classic actor coverage.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1 is self-contained for core classic actor coverage; its POM only requires scala-library and typesafe config transitively, and no Docker service or mandatory environment/system property is needed before meaningful tests can run.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Generate tests against APIs actually present in pekko-actor_2.13 2.0.0-M1, such as classic ActorSystem, Props, AbstractActor, supervision, serialization/configuration, and Patterns.ask. Do not reuse the removed org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedProps, or TypedActorExtension APIs from the 1.1.5 tests; adding pekko-actor-typed would not restore those old APIs and would test a separate artifact.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 1.1.5 tests and metadata reference TypedActor/TypedActorExtension classes that are absent from the 2.0.0-M1 jar; this is an API-removal/test-porting issue, not a setup issue.\",\n    \"Pekko documentation recommends pekko-testkit for conventional actor unit tests, but core actor behavior can still be exercised without adding it, so it is not required as deterministic setup.\",\n    \"If future tests intentionally cover DNS resolver internals, they may need the existing add-exports JVM/native flag for sun.net.dns access, but DNS coverage is not required for baseline meaningful actor coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07a140bfcbb044b5016a42ed1c0494819587caae021f580bd8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 782, "output": 1369, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33895, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782770956815, "responseId": "resp_07a140bfcbb044b5016a42ed0d4e4c8195a9814df43b25e129"}, "toolResults": []}
